examples.content:
Chop 1/16 cup basil. Peel an onion. Dice 1/4 cup of onion. Peel one garlic clove and mince it. In a large pot, heat 1 tbsp olive oil over medium heat. Add the onion and garlic and cook for 2-3 minutes, until softened. Stir in 1/4 can crushed tomatoes and 1/2 cup vegetable broth. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat and simmer for 2 minutes. Stir in the 1/8 cup heavy cream and 1/16 cup chopped fresh basil. Season with 1/4 tsp salt and 1/4 tsp pepper. Serve immediately.
